title: Doctor Who Review - School Reunion
body:
This story basically has nothing going for it aside from the obvious (which I’ll get to in a bit). It’s a fairly standard story set on Earth, where Mickey calls up the Doctor and Rose (ugh) back home to investigate a school, which is being run by Anthony Head’s character. He is the leader of the Krillitanes, who are using childrens’ minds to try and crack a code that will let them warp reality. To be honest, the character’s writing is nothing special, but Head really makes the part seem more alien even when he’s the only one in human form.

But let’s get to the thing that everyone knows this for: Sarah Jane and K-9 (I still find it weird that K-9 was brought back with Sarah Jane, but that’s just the leftovers from K-9 & Company so really I should blame JNT rather than RTD). And for a companion that I never thought was particuarly special and a tin dog that I haven’t seen much of, they work really well. Sarah Jane becomes less generic than she was during the Hinchcliffe Era, and K-9 is really fun as a nod back to the Williams Era. They properly tie the show to the Classic era, and especially what is considered the “golden age” of Doctor Who.

The stand-out of this story is really Mickey. This is the story where he leaves earth and joins the TARDIS team, and he is still my favourite companion of this early Davies era. He succeeds in blocking some of the flirting between Ten and Rose, and (despite being comic relief sometimes) really comes into his own when fighting the Cybermen in that parallel universe.

7/10. A fairly average story elevated by some fun returning characters from the Hinchcliffe and Williams eras.
